        "<p>Merry Little Breezes.</p>\n<p>Old Mother West Wind came down from the Purple Hills to the Green</p>\n<p>Meadows and as she walked she crooned a song:</p>\n<p>â€œShips upon the ocean wait;</p>\n<h3>I must hurry, hurry on!</h3>\n<p>Mills are idle if I'm late;</p>\n<h3>I must hurry, hurry on.â€</h3>\n",
